has been reported from fresh and slightly brackish waters, in wells and ditches, amongst vegetation and bottom deposits (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFCBFFAE6397FB24C637FA89" author="Bartsch, I." box="[720,876,1266,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" pagination="490 - 510" refId="ref9443" refString="Bartsch, I. (2011) North American freshwater Halacaridae (Acari): literature survey and new records. International Journal of Acarology, 37, 490 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647954.2010.525528" type="journal article" year="2011">Bartsch 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Future analysis based on molecular data should confirm or disprove the taxonomic status of populations of this species from wide geographical areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB61059FFCBFFAE6180FAECC58EFA61" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFCBFFAE6180FAECC427FAD0" author="Bartsch, I." box="[199,380,1338,1365]" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" pagination="443 - 450" refId="ref8949" refString="Bartsch, I. (1999 d) Two new freshwater mites of the genus Limnohalacarus (Halacaridae: Acari) from Australia. Records of the Western Australian Museum, 19, 443 - 450." type="journal article" year="1999">Bartsch (1999d)</bibRefCitation>
reported a new 
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCBFFAE6376FAECC7B2FAD1" box="[561,745,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Limonhalacarus</emphasis>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCBFFAE6200FAEDC69CFAD1" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1999" box="[839,967,1338,1364]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Limnohalacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCBFFAE6200FAEDC69CFAD1" box="[839,967,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">L. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Kimberley, 
<collectingRegion id="49CDDEBBFFCBFFAE65C9FAEDC00DFAD1" box="[1166,1366,1338,1365]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
based on a single female specimen. 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCBFFAE60ABFA88C655FAFD" box="[492,782,1374,1400]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Limonhalacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCBFFAE60ABFA88C655FAFD" box="[492,782,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">Limonhalacarus australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar with 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCBFFAE62B9FA89C1C8FAFD" authorityName="Viets" authorityYear="1940" box="[1022,1171,1374,1400]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Limnohalacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cultellatus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCBFFAE62B9FA89C1C8FAFD" box="[1022,1171,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">L. cultellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCBFFAE64C1FA89C5A2FA19" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Limonhalacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCBFFAE64C1FA89C5A2FA19" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="308">L. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be collected and studied to know the variability in characters e.g., number of genital acetabula. Future studies at morphological and molecular levels should investigate the status of the different species/populations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
